\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I have to do it but I don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know what it means.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What he would say to god.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Why is there something instead of nothing? Why inflict sickness? Why force a child through trauma and make it something unrecoverable. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 peace in this chaos?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 time and space?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Do You love me?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Do You see me}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What is in me that You want to heal}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Running up into the absuridty of existence.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 All compressed down to a simple, tearful, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The moment his question left his lips, it peeled open, and all the variegated forms of \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91why\u8217\'92 spilled out. The bright intelligence picked these up and poked them into a neat bouquet. It handed them back. Mandri stared into them and saw how those questions weren\u8217\'92t questions at all but a set of propositions instantiating his own model of the world. At points, that model was incoherent, and so, at points he had his questions. The problem was geometrical. His questions could not be answered, only subsumed by a change in shape. And this revelation went further down, to the lowest level, to dig up the roots of language which moulded that geometry. Words pulled up quick because there were no roots. Every word was  ignorance. This was his \u8216\'91why\u8217\'92.  voice took the length of that measure and tried to map it onto omniscience. He\u8217\'92d built a structure out of words, and there were stray ends. Why? That \u8216\'91why\u8217\'92 was his. He demanded answers from himself. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Dipped into the waters of true knowledge, and submerged, he went completely blank. That all mind could only exist in a state of ignorance. None of this had been communicated to him. God had not touched him. He had come to this all by himself, and so even this, what felt like Truth, was merely a product of his own ignorance, a plant in the field of possible, sprouting questions. And what happend next, is that he was plucked, smelled, delighted in, an invincible joy, and then cast aside. To god, he was a wildflower. That\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s what he was, a wildflower.}
